## Understand the faults and have a workaround

Nothing is perfect. 

For example, this blog is written in GitHub. I've been working directly in the web-hosted repository (not in a locally cloned repo using a text editor) and spell checking is nonexistent. This makes sense because repos are mostly used to host code, not content. 
